external_knowledge:
- "literary treasures" metaphorically refers to books;
- "creators who spun the threads of these tales" metaphorically refers to the authors of the books;
- "realms these sagas inhabit" metaphorically refers to the genres of the books.

- "Leading stars" refers to the top-performing books;
- "Constellation of literature" is a metaphor for a genre;
- "Top five books by sales" means ranking the books within each genre based on the total quantity sold, and selecting the top five.

sql:
SELECT AVG(num_books_sold) AS average_books_per_customer
FROM (
  SELECT customer_id, COUNT(book_id) AS num_books_sold
  FROM sales
  GROUP BY customer_id
);
